# Tracker Signals

This is a merge-safe template only.

If the repository already has `TRACKER_SIGNALS.md`, do not overwrite it blindly. Merge any useful rules from this template into the existing file.

## Purpose

`TRACKER_SIGNALS.md` documents tracker-specific parameter meanings, especially Gator/GPS telemetry fields that appear inside the `params` column.

## Rules

- Treat this file as authoritative for tracker parameter interpretation.
- Do not guess unknown signal meanings.
- Preserve unknown `params` values as raw text.
- If a signal meaning is uncertain, mark it as uncertain.
- If a signal is device/vendor-specific, document the source.

## Example Signal Table

| Signal | Meaning | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| gpslev | GPS satellite/level indicator | integer | Confirm exact vendor meaning before relying on it |
| gsmlev | GSM signal level | integer | Confirm scale before deriving quality |
| hdop | Horizontal dilution of precision | float | Lower is generally better |
| pdop | Position dilution of precision | float | Lower is generally better |
| io66 | Device-specific IO field | unknown | Preserve raw unless documented |
| io67 | Device-specific IO field | unknown | Preserve raw unless documented |

## Agent Rule

Agents must not convert unknown tracker IO fields into semantic labels unless the meaning is documented here.
